title.6: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #2
title.41: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #8
title.79: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #1

description.0: How can Hawkeye stop the Bullet Biker if he can’t even keep up with him?!  Plus, a Hollywood tale featuring Wonder Man!
description.1: Is it burglary? Is it blackmail? Or is it both? Spidey's late-night investigation of an Empire State University lab uncovers a high-stakes plot that pits him against both Killer Shrike and the Tinkerer!
description.2: Edwin Jarvis plays hero in this special Avengers issue! After the team disassembles, Jarvis is left to his own devices in New York City, and moves in with his elderly mother. Featuring Jarvis' adventures with a TV repairman, a delayed subway, and a pay phone! Edwin Jarvis, the Avenger!
description.3: Flag Smasher's got a problem, and he wants Captain America's help. But when Captain America turns out not to be the one Flag Smasher knows, the stage is set for a battle royal!
description.10: He is the robotic bounty hunter Death's Head. He is a mercenary for hire. And if you're within his range, then all you need to know is that escape is futile.
description.12: His power still growing, the Star Child uses it to prevent death on Earth once and for all! But a deathless world isn't the wonderful place it sounds like, and to reverse it Ken must pay the ultimate price!
description.13: Peter's business trip to San Diego is cut short when the villainous Boomerang makes an explosive entrance! Fists fly and webs sling in this showdown at Silicon Beach!
description.14: Speedball confronts an on-the-lam convict following his stealing spree! Will Leaper Logan be able to hop away to his next heist?
description.15: A new evil rears its head! Watch as the West Coast Avengers face off against the menace known only as the DEFILER!
description.16: Doctor Strange is dead! Or so the world believes, as the work of a Sorcerer Supreme is never done! Strange’s newest task is also his most dire: defeat the dread DORMAMMU!
description.20: Typhoid Mary has hit her mark! Daredevil's in dire straits when Typhoid's rogues gallery comes out of the woodwork. The Man Without Fear is usually 'swinging blindly'...but this time the saying couldn't be more true!
description.21: The Warwolves of Mojoverse are attacking London, and Excalibur answers the call! Kitty and Rachel take on metallic critters that steal people's 'skin'.
description.22: Mr. Fixit and Spider-Man are having what you might call a communication breakdown. But then again, communicating was never one of Mr. Fixit's strong suits...
description.23: An acclaimed sculptor who creates incredibly beautiful and lifelike statues! The mysterious disappearances of scores of young women! A man seeking immortality. Another man seeking vengeance! How are all these things linked? Iron Man knows and that's why he's launching one of the most desperate manhunts in his life. For the man behind it all is the Grey Gargoyle!
description.25: Magik transforms into her full demonic form as the Darkchilde! Meanwhile, the rescue mission for Lila Cheney hits a major snag…
description.26: Captured by Grog! Thor, Hogun, and Black Knight must find a way to escape before Seth and Loki manage to doom Asgard once and for all!
description.27: Things go haywire when Peter Parker travels to Las Vegas on a book tour. Featuring Mr. Fixit!
description.30: Battle of the Brutes! The Thing finds himself in a full on fist match against the Grey Hulk. Things sky rocket when a second green-skinned enters the fray! Is Ben Grimm strong enough to take down two hulks?!
description.33: Galactic entities, even more powerful than the mighty Galactus, threaten to destroy the universe as we know it! How can even the Silver Surfer with the combined power of the Fantastic Four hope to defeat such beings!?
description.34: Super Hero Vs. Super Hero! With Wolverine in custody, the X-Men and Alpha Flight clash for their stake over Logan!
description.35: On the anniversary of his family's death, Frank Castle flies a kite. With the memory of his loved ones haunting his every breath (and blow), the Punisher remains locked in his quest for vengeance. The next name in Castle's war journal? Mobster Hector Montoya- the man responsible for Punisher's loss.
description.44: Hawkeye may be out of his weight-class as he has to duel with the Abomination!  Plus, a scintillating Yellowjacket adventure!
description.45: Mary Jane is missing! And the web-slinger finds more than he bargained for when his hunt for his wife leads him smack into the Taskmaster!
description.46: In order to get his wife back from Jonathan Caesar, Spidey must fight his way past the bizarre double menace of Styx and Stone!
description.47: She-Hulk takes her leave from the team after feeling guilty over the things she did under Druid's control, while Thor and Black Knight decide to leave the team to attend to more pressing matters in Asgard. Will the Avengers be able to withstand losing core members of their team all at once?
description.48: When Right Winger and Left Winger exposed the new Captain America's secret identity, they caused the death of his parents! So now, the new Cap is looking for Right Winger and Left Winger, and he's planning to make them pay!
description.49: The Power Pack must lay low on their powers when they come across a gang of runners and arsonists!
description.50: The Dragon's Claws meet cyborg mercenary/assassin Death's Head, and all bets for survival are off!
description.52: Thor crash lands on the planet Pangoria, and immediately has his hands full! Between Pegas the planetary warlord, and Exitar the murderous Celestial, how will the Thunder God survive this harrowing world?
description.53: The wall-crawler senses that his sometimes-ally, sometimes-enemy Punisher is in grave danger, and travels to Dallas to help! But when he arrives, he's faced with a mind-controlled Frank Castle - out for spider-blood!
description.54: Robbie puts the kibosh on a sticky-fingered thief who has set out to rob Dr. Haven’s lab!
description.55: A TEAM…TORN! Mockingbird, Moon Knight and Tigra leave the West Coast Avengers! How will the team withstand this devastating split? And is there someone sinister behind this schism?
description.56: The WCA split up for a two-pronged assault on the High Evolutionary! Hawkeye, Wonder Man, Vision, and the Scarlet Witch may have experience, and Mockingbird, Moon Knight, and Tigra may be relentless and vicious, but can either team stand against the Evolutionary's incredible power?
description.62: Typhoid assembles a ragtag crew of villains for her final takedown of Daredevil. Karen Page slips into an investigative role, while Mary grows ever more desperate in her possession of Matt. Will Kingpin have the final say?
description.63: The world believes the X-Men have fallen, but this is only the beginning! Kitty Pryde, Rachel Summers, and Nightcrawler form Excalibur, premiere super hero team of the United Kingdom! Captain Britain leads the pack with shape-shifting lover Meggan. Will the team survive the coming days of terror?
description.64: The Absorbing Man is hired to take down the gangster Berengetti and his bodyguard, Mr. Fixit!
description.65: There's a new sculptor taking the West Coast by storm. However, his statues mask a deadly secret. Can Iron Man uncover the mystery of the "living statues" in time?
description.67: Lovely alien Gosamyr plays the New Mutants against each other, distracting everyone from their primary mission - tracking down Lila Cheney who is still in Spyder's web!
description.68: Seth's hordes begin their invasion of Asgard!
description.72: Doctor Doom vs. the Beyonder! The Molecule Man joins the fray! A whirlwind of cosmic forces beyond imagining! And the Fantastic Four are swept up right smack in the middle of it!
description.74: The Invisible Woman has been taken over by her Malice persona once more and only the Silver Surfer and Mr. Fantastic can save her!
description.75: After seeing footage of the X-Men battling the Mandroids in Japan, the Canadian Prime Minister demands to recruit Wolverine for his special ops government agency! Guest-starring Alpha Flight!
description.76: Hawkeye is severely outnumbered as mind-controlled henchmen keep him from stopping his real foe!  Plus, the Prince of Power Hercules in solo action!
description.86: Once, Empire State University cut off the funding for his insect research. Now, Humbug's back to take his revenge! And lurking in the background is one of Spidey's oldest foes! Plus, to top it all off, what are the sinister Jonathan Caesar's evil intentions toward Mary Jane?
description.87: Chicago! Spider-Man versus the Chameleon! And Mary Jane- kidnapped!
description.88: Dr. Druid is playing mind games with She-Hulk, and Thor and Black Knight confront him about it. Meanwhile, Nebula secures control over all three of the Avengers' minds.
description.89: The Government isn't happy with the new Captain America - not after he slaughtered the Watchdogs! They've given him one chance to make amends... by rounding up the mutant Resistants, with Battle Star and the ex-evil mutants of Freedom Force at his side!
description.90: Watch as Wolverine is transformed into a Brood!
description.92: The birth of Bengal! Daredevil must protect a Vietnam veteran from a Vietnamese vigilante out for revenge. Will Daredevil stalk his prey as swiftly as Bengal?
description.93: Spider-Man chases Tombstone all the way to Atlanta, where the final showdown happens at last! Can Peter avenge his friend Joe?
description.94: The West Coast Avengers' new target is a shocking one…HANK PYM!? Why has the team of heroes turned on their scientist-turned-adventurer comrade?
description.99: Someone is trying to take down the biggest gangster in Las Vegas. And the gangster's body guard seems to have a lot in common with the currently missing Hulk!

4.text: As if mankind's war against the alien Horde wasn't bad enough, now the Morituri force must face the appearance of two new alien races! And to make matters worse, one of those aliens promises to make the Morituri more dangerous to mankind than the Horde!

5.text: Andy Clark and Jim Rubino are in Khe Sanh to get help for Rubino's wounded leg. But Khe Sanh is the target for one of the first strikes in the Tet Offensive! Can they rescue an ancient city from the North Vietnamese onslaught?

6.text: Dagger is blinded and her condition may be permanent! Cloak meets Detective Nales at Holy Ghost Church, where he is used as a gateway to another dimension.

7.text: The Kingpin employs a gang of teenagers to do his every bidding. Frank Castle goes undercover as a substitute teacher to disrupt this gun and drugs supply chain!

8.text: Drug dealers are planning to take control over the neighborhood and the Wolfpack must defeat them.

11.text: Madelyne Pryor harnesses the Phoenix Force, and the X-Men siege the Magistrate citadel!

12.text: His power still growing, the Star Child uses it to prevent death on Earth once and for all! But a deathless world isn't the wonderful place it sounds like, and to reverse it Ken must pay the ultimate price!

28.text: Angel, now the winged beast known as Death, makes his way to Cameron Hodge's hideout on a mission to rescue his girlfriend Candy Southern. But Hodge has other plans for the flying mutant...
Angel, now the winged beast known as Death, makes his way to Cameron Hodge's hideout on a mission to rescue his girlfriend Candy Southern. But Hodge has other plans for the flying mutant...

31.text: Rogue and Logan have lost their powers-can they survive long enough for the X-Men to make it to Genosha?

32.text: Welcome to Madripoor, the best place to find trouble and lose yourself in it! It's a key piece of Wolverine's past, and death awaits him there in #1 of his first ongoing series!

36.text: Roy and Dann Thomas present the Saga of the Sub-Mariner, Prince of Atlantis! The origin of Namor, retold in full!

37.text: In this epic conclusion, Nick persuades Madame Hydra to lead him to the source of the conspiracy… S.H.I.E.L.D’S Satellite!

38.text: Hardcase became a Morituri in a search for honor and glory. But when he finally finds them, he discovers that honor and glory are actually two very different things!

39.text: North Vietnam launches the Tet Offensive! This seems like the beginning of the end for the United States!

40.text: Following his prison break-IN, Castle must break OUT! He has the help of a couple new friends…but will their combined efforts be enough?

41.text: First appearance of the Young Gods! The High Evolutionary apprehends Gwen Stacy’s clone in an attempt to harness the secret of cloning.

42.text: As Wolfpack tries to rid their neighborhood of all drug dealers, they run into a samurai who turns out to be one of their deadliest assassins yet.

51.text: The X-Men uncover the truth of Genegineer David Moreau's mutate process, and Rogue and Wolverine attempt to escape Genoshan prison!

53.text: The wall-crawler senses that his sometimes-ally, sometimes-enemy Punisher is in grave danger, and travels to Dallas to help! But when he arrives, he's faced with a mind-controlled Frank Castle - out for spider-blood!

54.text: Robbie puts the kibosh on a sticky-fingered thief who has set out to rob Dr. Haven’s lab!

55.text: A TEAM…TORN! Mockingbird, Moon Knight and Tigra leave the West Coast Avengers! How will the team withstand this devastating split? And is there someone sinister behind this schism?

56.text: The WCA split up for a two-pronged assault on the High Evolutionary! Hawkeye, Wonder Man, Vision, and the Scarlet Witch may have experience, and Mockingbird, Moon Knight, and Tigra may be relentless and vicious, but can either team stand against the Evolutionary's incredible power?

70.text: The Alliance of Evil has an anti-mutant message that it wants the world to hear, in the form of ultimate destruction! But Jean Grey and Iceman have a better idea and it involves stopping the Alliance in their tracks!

The Alliance of Evil has an anti-mutant message that it wants the world to hear, in the form of ultimate destruction! But Jean Grey and Iceman have a better idea and it involves stopping the Alliance in their tracks!

73.text: The Genoshan Press Gang goes to Australia to retrieve a former Genoshan nurse whose mutant gene has awoken. Who will be ensnared in their net along the way?

77.text: The Horde has destroyed his family. With his life in ruins, a young man may have no choice but to undergo the Morituri process and gain super powers...even though it's going to cost him his life!

78.text: As we near the Christmas Truce of 1967, a new recruit learns that spending the holidays far away from home can make for a pretty "Blue Christmas"!

79.text: Dagger is corrupted by Night’s Darkness and must battle Jean Grey, Iceman and Beast of X-Factor. Cloak is trapped and must escape to help Dagger!

80.text: Frank Castle must take down a murderous cult leader…from inside prison walls!

81.text: A fight breaks out between two gangs in South Bronx and one of them has high-caliber weaponry. Is it enough to wipe out Wolfpack?

83.text: At last! T’Challa begins his spiritual quest to battle the Panther Spirit…with the future of Wakanda at stake.

84.text: In the heart of the Himalayas, Nick and Madame Hydra delve deeper into the mystery of the Delta Equation and the corruption that's been eating away at S.H.I.E.L.D.!

85.text: The epic conclusion to the monumental collaboration between Stan Lee and Moebius starring the Sentinel of the Spaceways - the Silver Surfer!
